100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 11, 1926, in a significant diplomatic move, the United States and the Soviet Union engaged in talks regarding the recognition of the Soviet government. Meanwhile, in Europe, unrest continued as strikes erupted in Germany over economic hardships, further challenging the Weimar Republics stability. In the realm of science, news of advancements in radio technology sparked excitement for the future of communication.
